
SETUP
-----
1. Make sure pi_sensor.py is already running on the Raspberry Pi.
2. Ensure you have certs/server.crt in the same directory as second_terminal.py.
3. Set PI_HOST in second_terminal.py to the Pi's Tailscale IP address.
4. Run: python3 second_terminal.py


- The arm will NOT move if E-Stop is active.
- Always home the arm (h) before starting a session.
- The arm moves smoothly to target — it does NOT snap instantly.
- All arm movement is blocked while E-Stop is active.
- Press e to activate E-Stop in an emergency.
  The robot will stop immediately.
  Press e again (from Operator 1) to resume.

----------------------------------------------------
E-STOP
----------------------------------------------------
  e       Activate E-Stop (stops robot + arm immediately)

----------------------------------------------------
ARM CONTROLS
----------------------------------------------------

  h       Home — moves all joints to 90 degrees (neutral position)

  BASE (rotates arm left/right):
  j       Base rotate LEFT  (moves to 60 degrees)
  r       Base rotate RIGHT (moves to 120 degrees)
  Range:  30 to 150 degrees

  SHOULDER (raises/lowers upper arm):
  i       Shoulder UP   (moves to 120 degrees)
  k       Shoulder DOWN (moves to 60 degrees)
  Range:  40 to 140 degrees

  ELBOW (raises/lowers forearm):
  u       Elbow UP   (moves to 120 degrees)
  o       Elbow DOWN (moves to 60 degrees)
  Range:  20 to 160 degrees

  GRIPPER (opens/closes claw):
  n       Gripper OPEN  (moves to 90 degrees)
  m       Gripper CLOSE (moves to 10 degrees)
  Range:  10 to 90 degrees

----------------------------------------------------
QUIT
----------------------------------------------------
  q       Quit second_terminal.py

----------------------------------------------------
INCOMING ROBOT STATUS (displayed automatically)
----------------------------------------------------
  The terminal will print robot status automatically:
  - [robot] Status: RUNNING / STOPPED
  - [robot] Speed updated -> X/255 (Y%)
  - [robot] Color: R=X Hz, G=Y Hz, B=Z Hz
  - [robot] Debug: <message from Arduino>

----------------------------------------------------
TYPICAL PICK-UP SEQUENCE
----------------------------------------------------
1. h         — home the arm first
2. j or r    — rotate base to face the object
3. i / k     — adjust shoulder height
4. u / o     — adjust elbow to reach object
5. n         — open gripper
6. o         — lower elbow over object
7. m         — close gripper to grab
8. i         — lift shoulder up
9. r or j    — rotate base to delivery position
10. n        — open gripper to drop

